<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE of 22 March 1977 to facilitate the effective exercise by lawyers of freedom to provide services (77/249/EEC) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 77/249/EM&Uuml; &Otilde;igusteenuste osutamise vabaduse tulemuslikuma elluviimise kohta </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> 22. m&auml;rts 1977 Euroopa &Uuml;henduste N&otilde;ukogu, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Articles 57 and 66 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikleid 57 ja 66, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to the Treaty, any restriction on the provision of services which is based on nationality or on conditions of residence has been prohibited since the end of the transitional period; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: k&otilde;ik kodakondsuse v&otilde;i elukoha alusel kehtestatud piirangud teenuste osutamisel on asutamislepingu kohaselt p&auml;rast &uuml;leminekuperioodi l&otilde;ppemist keelatud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this Directive deals only with measures to facilitate the effective pursuit of the activities of lawyers by way of provision of services; whereas more detailed measures will be necessary to facilitate the effective exercise of the right of establishment; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev direktiiv k&auml;sitleb &uuml;ksnes neid meetmeid, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on h&otilde;lbustada juristide aktiivset tegevust &otilde;igusteenuste osutamisel; asutamis&otilde;iguse tulemuslikumaks rakendamiseks on vaja &uuml;ksikasjalikumaid meetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas if lawyers are to exercise effectively the freedom to provide services host Member States must recognize as lawyers those persons practising the profession in the various Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> &otilde;igusteenuste osutamise vabaduse tulemuslikumaks elluviimiseks peavad vastuv&otilde;tvad liikmesriigid juristidena tunnustama isikuid, kes osutavad liikmesriikides &otilde;igusteenuseid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, since this Directive solely concerns provision of services and does not contain provisions on the mutual recognition of diplomas, a person to whom the Directive applies must adopt the professional title used in the Member State in which he is established, hereinafter referred to as "the Member State from which he comes", </inglise>
<eesti> kuna k&auml;esolev direktiiv puudutab &uuml;ksnes teenuste osutamist ega sisalda s&auml;tteid vastastikuse diplomite tunnustamise kohta, siis isikud, kelle suhtes k&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse, peavad kasutama seda ametinimetust, mis k&auml;ibib tema p&auml;ritoluriigis, edaspidi "riik, kust asjaomane isik on tulnud". </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Each Member State shall recognize as a lawyer for the purpose of pursuing the activities specified in Article 1 (1) any person listed in paragraph 2 of that Article. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad tunnustama juristina artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tegevuse m&otilde;ttes iga k&otilde;nealuse artikli l&otilde;ikes 2 loetletud isikut. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> A person referred to in Article 1 shall adopt the professional title used in the Member State from which he comes, expressed in the language or one of the languages, of that State, with an indication of the professional organization by which he is authorized to practise or the court of law before which he is entitled to practise pursuant to the laws of that State. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 1 nimetatud isik peab kasutama ametinimetust, mis k&auml;ibib selles riigis, kust ta on tulnud, v&auml;ljendatuna selle riigi keeles v&otilde;i keeltes, viitega kutseorganisatsioonile, kuhu ta kuulub, v&otilde;i kohtule, kus ta selle riigi seaduste kohaselt v&otilde;ib klienti esindada. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Activities relating to the representation of a client in legal proceedings or before public authorities shall be pursued in each host Member State under the conditions laid down for lawyers established in that State, with the exception of any conditions requiring residence, or registration with a professional organization, in that State. (1) OJ No C 103, 5.10.1972, p. 19 and OJ No C 53, 8.3.1976, p. 33. (2) OJ No C 36, 28.3.1970, p. 37 and OJ No C 50, 4.3.1976, p. 17. </inglise>
<eesti> Kliendi esindamine kohtumenetluses v&otilde;i suhtlemisel avaliku v&otilde;imu organitega peab toimuma vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis sealsetele juristidele kehtestatud tingimuste kohaselt, v&auml;lja arvatud n&otilde;ue elukoha v&otilde;i kutseorganisatsiooni kuulumise kohta vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> A lawyer pursuing these activities shall observe the rules of professional conduct of the host Member State, without prejudice to his obligations in the Member State from which he comes. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud tegevustega tegelev jurist peab j&auml;rgima vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis kehtivaid kutsealase k&auml;itumise reegleid, sealjuures vastuollu minemata kohustustega selles liikmesriigis, kust ta on tulnud. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> When these activities are pursued in the United Kingdom, "rules of professional conduct of the host Member State" means the rules of professional conduct applicable to solicitors, where such activities are not reserved for barristers and advocates. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui nimetatud tegevustega tegeldakse &Uuml;hendkuningriigis, tuleb "vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis kehtivate kutsealase k&auml;itumise reeglite" all m&otilde;ista &otilde;igusn&otilde;ustajate ("solicitor") kohta kehtivaid reegleid, kui k&otilde;nealune tegevus ei ole reserveeritud vandeadvokaatidele ("barrister") ja advokaatidele ("advocate"). </eesti>
<inglise> Otherwise the rules of professional conduct applicable to the latter shall apply. </inglise>
<eesti> Viimasel juhul kohaldatakse vandeadvokaatide ja advokaatide suhtes kehtivaid kutsealase k&auml;itumise reegleid. </eesti>
<inglise> However, barristers from Ireland shall always be subject to the rules of professional conduct applicable in the United Kingdom to barristers and advocates. </inglise>
<eesti> Iirimaalt p&auml;rinevatele vandeadvokaatide ("barrister") suhtes kohaldatakse alati kutsealase k&auml;itumise reegleid, mis kehtivad &Uuml;hendkuningriigis vandeadvokaatide ja advokaatide kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> When these activities are pursued in Ireland "rules of professional conduct of the host Member State" means, in so far as they govern the oral presentation of a case in court, the rules of professional conduct applicable to barristers. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui nimetatud tegevustega tegeldakse Iirimaal, siis selles osas, mis puudutab asja suulist arutamist kohtus, tuleb "vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis kehtivate kutsealase k&auml;itumise reeglite" all m&otilde;ista vandeadvokaatide ("barrister") kohta kehtivaid kutsealase k&auml;itumise reegleid. </eesti>
<inglise> In all other cases the rules of professional conduct applicable to solicitors shall apply. </inglise>
<eesti> Muudel juhtudel kohaldatakse &otilde;igusn&otilde;ustajate ("solicitor") kohta kehtivaid kutsealase k&auml;itumise reegleid. </eesti>
<inglise> However, barristers and advocates from the United Kingdom shall always be subject to the rules of professional conduct applicable in Ireland to barristers. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriigist p&auml;rinevatele vandeadvokaatide ja advokaatide suhtes kohaldatakse alati kutsealase k&auml;itumise reegleid, mis kehtivad Iirimaal vandeadvokaatide kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> A lawyer pursuing activities other than those referred to in paragraph 1 shall remain subject to the conditions and rules of professional conduct of the Member State from which he comes without prejudice to respect for the rules, whatever their source, which govern the profession in the host Member State, especially those concerning the incompatibility of the exercise of the activities of a lawyer with the exercise of other activities in that State, professional secrecy, relations with other lawyers, the prohibition on the same lawyer acting for parties with mutually conflicting interests, and publicity. </inglise>
<eesti> Jurist, kes tegeleb l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatust erineva tegevusega, peab j&auml;rgima kutsealase k&auml;itumise tingimusi ja reegleid, mis kehtivad selles riigis, kust ta on tulnud, sealjuures vastuollu minemata nende reeglitega, mis reguleerivad vastavat elukutset vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis, eriti reeglitega, mis k&auml;sitlevad juristi tegevuse &uuml;hildamatust teiste tegevustega k&otilde;nealuses riigis, ametisaladust, suhteid teiste juristidega, keeldu esindada vastandlike huvidega pooli ja avalikustamist. </eesti>
<inglise> The latter rules are applicable only if they are capable of being observed by a lawyer who is not established in the host Member State and to the extent to which their observance is objectively justified to ensure, in that State, the proper exercise of a lawyer's activities, the standing of the profession and respect for the rules concerning incompatibility. </inglise>
<eesti> Viimati nimetatud reegleid kohaldatakse, kui juristil, kes ei p&auml;rine vastuv&otilde;tvast liikmesriigist, on v&otilde;imalik neid j&auml;rgida, ja sellises ulatuses, kui nende j&auml;rgimine on objektiivselt p&otilde;hjendatud, et tagada k&otilde;nealuses riigis juristide korrektne tegutsemine, elukutse hea maine ja &uuml;hildamatuse reeglite j&auml;rgimine. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> For the pursuit of activities relating to the representation of a client in legal proceedings, a Member State may require lawyers to whom Article 1 applies: - to be introduced, in accordance with local rules or customs, to the presiding judge and, where appropriate, to the President of the relevant Bar in the host Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriik v&otilde;ib kliendi kohtumenetluses esindamisega seotud tegevuste puhul n&otilde;uda juristidelt, kelle kohta kehtib artikkel 1, - et neid kohalike reeglite ja tavade kohaselt esitletaks kohtu eesistujale ja vajaduse korral vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi vastava advokatuuri esimehele; </eesti>
<inglise> - to work in conjunction with a lawyer who practises before the judicial authority in question and who would, where necessary, be answerable to that authority, or with an "avou&eacute;" or "procuratore" practising before it. </inglise>
<eesti> - et nad t&ouml;&ouml;taksid koos juristiga, kes v&otilde;ib esindada klienti k&otilde;nealuses kohtus ja on vajaduse korral selle ees vastutav, v&otilde;i koos selles kohtus tegutseva "avou&eacute;" v&otilde;i "procuratore'iga". </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Any Member State may exclude lawyers who are in the salaried employment of a public or private undertaking from pursuing activities relating to the representation of that undertaking in legal proceedings in so far as lawyers established in that State are not permitted to pursue those activities. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriik v&otilde;ib keelata avalik-&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i era&otilde;igusliku ettev&otilde;tjaga t&ouml;&ouml;suhtes oleva juristi tegevuse, mis on seotud ettev&otilde;tja esindamisega kohtumenetluses, juhul kui k&otilde;nealusest riigist p&auml;rineval juristil ei ole selline tegevus lubatud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authority of the host Member State may request the person providing the services to establish his qualifications as a lawyer. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi p&auml;dev organ v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda, et &otilde;igusteenuseid osutav isik t&otilde;endaks, et ta on jurist. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In the event of non-compliance with the obligations referred to in Article 4 and in force in the host Member State, the competent authority of the latter shall determine in accordance with its own rules and procedures the consequences of such non-compliance, and to this end may obtain any appropriate professional information concerning the person providing services. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui eiratakse vastuv&otilde;tvas liikmesriigis kehtivaid kohustusi, mida on nimetatud artiklis 4, peab selle riigi p&auml;dev organ tegema oma eeskirjade ja protseduuride kohaselt otsuse eiramise tagaj&auml;rgede suhtes, ja tal on sealjuures &otilde;igus hankida teenuseid osutava isiku kohta igasugust vajalikku ametialast informatsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall notify the competent authority of the Member State from which the person comes of any decision taken. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi p&auml;dev organ teatab k&otilde;igist oma otsustest p&auml;devale organile selles riigis, kust teenuseid osutav isik on tulnud. </eesti>
<inglise> Such exchanges shall not affect the confidential nature of the information supplied. </inglise>
<eesti> Edastatav informatsioon j&auml;&auml;b konfidentsiaalseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall bring into force the measures necessary to comply with this Directive within two years of its notification and shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi t&auml;itmiseks vajalikud meetmed j&otilde;ustama kahe aasta jooksul alates direktiivi teatavakstegemisest ning teatama sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall communicate to the Commission the texts of the main provisions of national law which they adopt in the field covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas vastuv&otilde;etavate peamiste siseriiklike &otilde;igusnormide teksti. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 22 March 1977. </inglise>
